<![endif]-->  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Symbol;">&middot;</span><span style="">&nbsp; </span>Day 27 - A movie that you wish you had seen in theatres</p>  Well, there are a lot of films that came out before I could see them when they came out. And there's films I dismissed that it turned out were really good. If there were no such things as DVDs maybe I'd wish I'd seen them at the cinema. But there's very few where I've thought &quot;OMG, I *wish* I'd seen this at the time.<br />For petty, childish reasons, I wish I'd seen <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0382932/">Ratatouille (2007)</a>, I'm not sure I exactly have a burning desire to see it, although I have heard it's very good, but I still haven't seen it. It's just, I realised the other day that it's the only Pixar film I never saw at the cinema. And I'm not exactly sure why...<br />I guess some of the classic Bond films, and action films like <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0095016/">Die Hard (1988)</a> would be good on the big screen, but it's not like it's not possible with a DVD and a big enough screen. The same goes for the <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0032138/">Wizard of Oz (1939)</a>, although I would love to have seen it when it came out and was fresh and exciting.<br />Which, I guess, leads me to my pick:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0080684/">The Empire Strikes Back (1980)</a><br /><br /><a href="http://pics.livejournal.com/niblick_iii/pic/000cs2x3/"><img border="0" src="http://pics.livejournal.com/niblick_iii/pic/000cs2x3/s320x240" style="width: 115px; height: 143px;" alt="" /></a><br /><br />Why do I wish I'd seen this at the cinema (I refuse to say &quot;in theatres&quot;, that's where I go to see live acting)? I'd have thought it would be obvious. I'd loved to have seen the plot twist (and do I really need to say which one?) back when it actually <em>was</em> a plot twist. When it was&nbsp; revaltion to shake the audience. Now, it's ubiquitous. People who've never seen the film knows what happens (even if they misquote it). Hell, I'm pretty sure kids know it before they even know what Star Wars <em>is</em>!!<br />And, hah, I managed to get the whole way through the post without mentioning that I meant the fact that Darth Vader is Luke's father...damn.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />

Well I missed posting yesterday because a couple of drinks after work for a guy's leaving do ended up with about six of us staying in the pub until closing. Since I'd been at the pub since about 20 past 5, I was rather un-sober by the time I got home. A great evening, getting to know my colleagues a bit more. Tequila happened and I demonstrated just how shit I am at pool. And this evening I went to see Scott Pilgrim again with the other new guy and the guy who's leaving. And it really sucks that they're the two people I've got on with best this week, and one of them isn't just leaving the company, he's emigrating to Australia. I think we could have been good friends. TBF, I'm just kind of surprised that he took the time and effort to talk to me and get to know me, I'm not sure many people would bother with someone who started in their last week.<br />So yeah, so was ever so more than slightly hung over this morning. Luckily, Friday is traditionally pub lunch day, where everyone goes to the pub and ends up taking at least 1 1/2 hours break. Plus I spent most of the day playing 20 questions over IRC.<br />But hey, I'm starting on actual work soon, and I had a meeting yesterday that, whilst it lasted all day a) got me another free lunch (also down the pub) and b) was actually quite interesting because it served as a really good introduction to the part of the project that I'll be working on.<br /><br />If I haven't said it before, I think I&nbsp;like this place. <br /><br />Oh yeah, and I should add to my list of mentals in my office. The guy who sits diagonally opposite me used to do cage fighting.<br /><br />All in all, it's been a pretty good first week, and from starting the week being terrified of having responsibility, I'm now kind of looking forward to doing some real work.<br /><br />And as I missed yesterday, a double dose of memeness.<br /><br /><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><meta name="ProgId" content="Word.Document"><meta name="Generator" content="Microsoft Word 11"><meta name="Originator" content="Microsoft Word 11"><link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:\Users\Michelle\AppData\Local\Temp\msohtml1\01\clip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
