<![endif]-->  <p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: Symbol;">&middot;</span><span style="">&nbsp; </span>Day 23 - Favourite animation</strong></p>  Another easy one.<br /><br /><br /><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0110357/">The Lion King (1994)</a><br /><br /><a href="http://pics.livejournal.com/niblick_iii/pic/000cgg8h/"><img border="0" src="http://pics.livejournal.com/niblick_iii/pic/000cgg8h/s320x240" style="width: 109px; height: 155px;" alt="" /></a><br /><br />Do I really need to explain this? It was my childhood. The story is good, characters that are lovable, awesome songs. It's the Lion King. What child growing up in the 90s didn't love this film? I probably still know all the words to Hakuna Matata. What a wonderful phrase. <br />I realised the other day that when someone says &quot;meerkat&quot; my immediate thought is Timon. My sisters think of comparethemeerkat.com<br /> <br />I just adore it. It's everything a Disney movie should be. Even The Lion Kind 2: Simba's Pride isn't too terrible (ok, it is but I like a couple of the songs from it)<br /><br /><br /><meta content="text/html; charset=utf-8" http-equiv="Content-Type"><meta content="Word.Document" name="ProgId"><meta content="Microsoft Word 11" name="Generator"><meta content="Microsoft Word 11" name="Originator"><link href="file:///C:\Users\Michelle\AppData\Local\Temp\msohtml1\01\clip_filelist.xml" rel="File-List" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
